examples.en: The four pillars bear the arch.
The steel pillars began to buckle.
The house was graced with arch and pillars.
Science eroded the pillars of superstition.
The roof is held up by massive stone pillars.
Eight massive stone pillars supported the roof.
Shopkeepers would once have been pillars of the Tory establishment.
One of the pillars of a civilized society must be that everyone has equal access to the legal system.
